question: What is the student code of conduct at Diné College?
What is the policy on travel and purchase approvals?
answer_text:
According to the provided context, the policy on travel and purchase approvals is as follows:

- All travel shall be authorized in advance by the approving official (Section A Authorizations and Responsibilities, REQUIREMENT FOR TRAVEL AUTHORIZATION).
- The authorization should be specific with respect to the purpose of travel, location, and dates (Section A Authorizations and Responsibilities, REQUIREMENT FOR TRAVEL AUTHORIZATION).
- Authorization of an uncustomary transportation method (e.g. charter airplane) will require the President's or Vice President's approval and a showing of cost feasibility (Section A Authorizations and Responsibilities, REQUIREMENT FOR TRAVEL AUTHORIZATION).
- Payment will be made in accordance with ACCOUNTS PAYABLE SCHEDULE OF DISBURSEMENTS for amounts over $100.00, and reimbursements less than $100.00 will be processed in accordance with the Payroll schedule (Fin P&P -Approved by BOR 03.11.2022_travel_Purchase.pdf).
- All travelers must attach an agenda at the time of submittal of Travel Authorization of the meeting, training, and conference, etc. that they are attending (Fin P&P -Approved by BOR 03.11.2022_travel_Purchase.pdf).
- The President shall sign Travel Authorizations for the Board of Regents (Fin P&P -Approved by BOR 03.11.2022_travel_Purchase.pdf).
- A Travel Authorization is required for all official travel (Fin P&P -Approved by BOR 03.11.2022_travel_Purchase.pdf).
- Blanket Travel Authorizations must be properly approved by an approving official (Fin P&P -Approved by BOR 03.11.2022_travel_Purchase.pdf).
